{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Jer|22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","chapter":22,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":1,"text":"This is what the Lord says: “Go down to the palace of the king of Judah and announce this word there.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":2,"text":"You are to say, ‘Hear the word of the Lord, king of Judah, you who sit on the throne of David —you, your officers, and your people who enter these gates.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":3,"text":"This is what the Lord says: Administer justice and righteousness. Rescue the victim of robbery from his oppressor. Don’t exploit or brutalize the resident alien, the fatherless, or the widow. Don’t shed innocent blood in this place.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":4,"text":"For if you conscientiously carry out this word, then kings sitting on David’s throne will enter through the gates of this palace riding on chariots and horses —they, their officers, and their people.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":5,"text":"But if you do not obey these words, then I swear by myself —this is the Lord’s declaration —that this house will become a ruin.’”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":6,"text":"For this is what the Lord says concerning the house of the king of Judah:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":7,"text":"I will set apart destroyers against you,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":8,"text":"“Many nations will pass by this city and ask one another, ‘Why did the Lord do such a thing to this great city?’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":9,"text":"They will answer, ‘Because they abandoned the covenant of the Lord their God and bowed in worship to other gods and served them.’”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":10,"text":"Do not weep for the dead;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":11,"text":"For this is what the Lord says concerning Shallum son of Josiah, king of Judah, who became king in place of his father Josiah, and who has left this place: “He will never return here again,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":12,"text":"but he will die in the place where they deported him, never seeing this land again.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":13,"text":"Woe for the one who builds his palace","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":14,"text":"who says, “I will build myself a massive palace,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":15,"text":"Are you a king because you excel in cedar?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":16,"text":"He took up the case of the poor and needy;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":17,"text":"But you have eyes and a heart for nothing","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":18,"text":"Therefore, this is what the Lord says concerning Jehoiakim son of Josiah, king of Judah:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":19,"text":"He will be buried like a donkey,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":20,"text":"Go up to Lebanon and cry out;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":21,"text":"I spoke to you when you were secure.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":22,"text":"The wind will take charge of all your shepherds,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":23,"text":"You residents of Lebanon,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":24,"text":"“As I live” —this is the Lord’s declaration —“though you, Coniah son of Jehoiakim, the king of Judah, were a signet ring on my right hand, I would tear you from it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":25,"text":"In fact, I will hand you over to those you dread, who intend to take your life, to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and the Chaldeans.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":26,"text":"I will hurl you and the mother who gave birth to you into another land, where neither of you were born, and there you will both die.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":27,"text":"They will never return to the land they long to return to.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":28,"text":"Is this man Coniah a despised, shattered pot,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":29,"text":"Earth, earth, earth,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:22:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":22,"verse":30,"text":"This is what the Lord says:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024